It doesn&#x27;t necessarily have to be semantic, but your visual styling should be in your style sheet. I&#x27;d do the following to achieve <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/cuCY0.png" rel="nofollow">http://i.stack.imgur.com/cuCY0.png</a> (assuming box model border box):<p>.story-large {
   width: 50%;
   @include scut-ratio-box;
}<p>.story-small {
   width: 25%;
   @include scut-ratio-box;
}<p>etc. I actually did something similar in production creating the Microsoft Surface 2 launch site in 2013: <a href="http://mikemaccana.com/images/work/screenshots/uncompromise-2.png" rel="nofollow">http://mikemaccana.com/images/work/screenshots/uncompromise-...</a>
